option.name: LAST_COMMIT_MESSAGE
option.value:
Guice integration with AtUnit working, finally understand what to do for DI, and how to circumvent it a bit in some of the unit tests.
Unit tests for basic global frequency counting and trait adoption work.
No infrastructure yet for auto-counting frequencies among a subset of the population, to do mesoscopic structure, but this is adequate for certain global frequency simulations like the Bentley et al. simulations.
Definitely have not tested the synchronized() aspect of trait adoption/unadoption, and there's some warnings, so I expect I might not be doing things completely properly there.
